                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-65-victim516 t18290115-65-viclabel312"></join> at the <placeName id="t18290115-65-crimeloc313">Castle Inn, Kingsland-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-65-crimeloc313" type="placeName" value="Castle Inn, Kingsland-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-65-crimeloc313" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-65-off310 t18290115-65-crimeloc313"></join>. The prisoners came there on the 10th of December, and slept together that night, within one room of me - in the morning, I saw them go down stairs - my box had been in my room, and I left it safe when I went out to work; I went afterwards, and found it had been broken open, and all these articles taken - I gave information, and recovered part of the property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-65-person518">
                  THOMAS 
                  HUNT
               <interp inst="t18290115-65-person518" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-65-person518" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-65-person518" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took Yardley for another robbery, on the 11th of December; on going to Bow-street, I heard of this robbery, and found on him this pair of scissors, 2 brooches, a handkerchief, and comb; I have since found two waistcoats.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, Yardley Pleading distress, and Legrave stating that Yardley had fetched the clothes into the bed-room, and that he considered them his property.</p>
